    <briefdescription>
<para>Complete description of one rolling readout: its sources, geometry, glyphs, flag. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>All spatial fields are mm; <ref refid="classOpenSkyhawk_1_1DrumDisplay" kindref="compound">DrumDisplay</ref> converts to px at configure() from the panel&apos;s getDisplayWidth()/getDisplayHeight(). <computeroutput>digitWidthMm</computeroutput> / <computeroutput>digitHeightMm</computeroutput> are the drum-window aperture. If the laid-out row is wider than the panel, auto-fit shrinks the pitch to the pixel width. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
